documentation.text:
@dev Reverts unless contractAddress points to a legit contract.
     Makes sure that the hash of the external code is neither 0x0 (not-yet created),
      nor an account without code: keccak256('') = 0xc5d2460186f7233c927e7db2dcc703c0e500b653ca82273b7bfad8045d85a470
     See EIP-1052 for more info
     This check is important to avoid delegateCall returning OK when delegating to nowhere

devdoc.details: Pattern: first, contracts-to-delegate-to info are added to this contract.Part of this info informs which function selector maps to each contract address.Second, in one atomic TX, we deactivate previous contracts, and activate newly added ones.

acceptCompany().details: The proposed owner uses this function to become the new owner

activateContracts(uint256[]).details: Activates a set of contracts, by adding an entry in the       _selectorToContractAddr mapping for each selector of the contract.

params.contractIds: The ids of the contracts to be activated

assertPointsToContract(address).details: Reverts unless contractAddress points to a legit contract.     Makes sure that the hash of the external code is neither 0x0 (not-yet created),      nor an account without code: keccak256('') = 0xc5d2460186f7233c927e7db2dcc703c0e500b653ca82273b7bfad8045d85a470     See EIP-1052 for more info     This check is important to avoid delegateCall returning OK when delegating to nowhere

constructor.details: Sets CompanyOwner and SuperUserStores proxy selectors in _contractsInfo[0], pointing to PROXY_DUMMY_ADDR

deactivateContracts(uint256[]).details: De-activates a set of contracts, by adding an entry in the       _selectorToContractAddr mapping for each selector of the contract.

params.contractIds: The ids of the contracts to be activated

proposeCompany(address).details: Proposes a new owner, who needs to later accept it

upgrade(uint256[],uint256[],address).details: Deactivates a set of contracts, and then activates another set,      in one single atomic transaction.       Note: it only removes the mapped selectors, not the contract info.

params.actContractIds: The ids of the contracts to be activated
params.deactContractIds: The ids of the contracts to be de-activated

devdoc.title: Holds all storage for all assets, and manages who to delegate the calls

setDirectory(address).notice: Directory is just an external contract used by synchornizers to read the addresses of all other contracts. The proxy just informs about the location of this contract, which is typically changed in an upgrade.

setSuperUser(address).notice: SuperUser manages the proxy contract. No need to propose/accept, since it can be changed by company.
